Step1:to  download the resources using this link

https://www.apache.org/dyn/closer.cgi/hadoop/common/hadoop-3.4.1/hadoop-3.4.1.tar.gz

 

to click the below link and download it

 hadoop-3.4.1.tar.gz 

Step2:to extract the file and paste it into c folder

 rename into hadoop

step3:go to search in main searchbar to type(edit the system environment variables)

to click that

step4: click rights side last environment variables button and at top user variables to click an

new button then select a java bin directory in c folder copy it and create a variable as JAVA_HOME then value as that copied java directory and paste it then create

C:\Java\jdk-1.8\bin

 

step5:top user variables to click an

new button then select a hadoop bin directory copy it and create a variable as HADOOP_HOME then value as that copied hadoop directory and paste it then create

C:\hadoop\bin

 

step7:then goto c folder: hadoop/etc/hadoop/ then click core-site.xml to change the configuration

<configuration>

  <property>

    <name>fs.defaultFS</name>

    <value>hdfs://localhost:9000</value>

  </property>

</configuration>

then change the hdfs-site.xml

<configuration>

    <property>

        <name>dfs.replication</name>

        <value>1</value>

    </property>

    <property>

        <name>dfs.namenode.name.dir</name>

        <value>C:\hadoop\data\namenode</value>

    </property>

    <property>

        <name>dfs.datanode.data.dir</name>

        <value>C:\hadoop\data\datanode</value>

    </property>

</configuration>

Then we should create the manual folder data inside the c\hadoop

Then within data it should be 2 folder creation datanode ,namenode

mapred-site.xml

Rename mapred-site.xml.template to mapred-site.xml and add the following content:



<configuration>

    <property>

        <name>mapreduce.framework.name</name>

        <value>yarn</value>

    </property>

</configuration>

 

Final configuration

yarn-site.xml

<configuration>
    <property>
        <name>yarn.nodemanager.aux-services</name>
        <value>mapreduce_shuffle</value>
    </property>
<property>
        <name>yarn.nodemanager.aux-services.mapreduce.shuffle.class</name>
        <value>org.apache.hadoop.mapred.shuffleHandler</value>
    </property>
</configuration>
Atlast we should change the hadoop environment

*Edit file C:/hadoop/etc/hadoop/hadoop-env.cmd to change the JAVA-HOME as our c folder java file directory

Finally download the hadoop configuration using the below link and extract it

https://github.com/MuhammadBilalYar/Hadoop-On-Window/blob/master/Hadoop%20Configuration.zip

then extract hadoop configuration file then open the bin folder files and copy all the files and paste the all files into c folder hadoop  folder bin (delete the existion  bin files and paste the hadoop configuration bin files)
